"```sql\nSELECT \n    SUM(CASE WHEN c.Currency = 'CZK' THEN ym.Consumption ELSE 0 END) - \n    SUM(CASE WHEN c.Currency = 'EUR' THEN ym.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Difference_in_Consumption\nFROM \n    yearmonth ym\nJOIN \n    customers c ON ym.CustomerID = c.CustomerID\nWHERE \n    SUBSTR(ym.Date, 1, 4) = '2012';\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the difference in gas consumption between customers who pay in CZK and those who pay in EUR for the year 2012. It uses the `yearmonth` table to get the consumption data and joins it with the `customers` table to filter by currency. The `SUBSTR` function is used to extract the year from the `Date` column in the `yearmonth` table."